Here is everything I found that may be missing or worth considering:\par
\par
Rules violation:\par
\par
\cf1 The ListView column headers "Destination" and "Source Path" are hardcoded English strings \emdash  they are NOT going through the locale system. Keys like files_col_destination and files_col_source need to be added to en_GB.txt and used in the ListView_InsertColumn calls.\par
\cf0\par
\b\f0 Missing Inno Setup functionality\b0\f1 :\par
\cf1\par
Per-file install flags \emdash  Inno's [Files] section supports a Flags: attribute per entry. None of these are currently exposed for individual files:\par
\par
ignoreversion \emdash  don't compare version info, always overwrite\par
onlyifdoesntexist \emdash  skip if file already exists at destination\par
confirmoverwrite \emdash  prompt user if file already exists\par
isreadme \emdash  marks a file to be shown in a README viewer post-install\par
deleteafterinstall \emdash  install to temp, auto-delete when installer exits (useful for bundled tools)\par
regserver \emdash  register a COM DLL after copying (regsvr32)\par
regtypelib \emdash  register a type library\par
sharedfile \emdash  increment Windows shared-file reference count (for shared DLLs)\par
restartreplace \emdash  if the file is locked, queue it for replacement on next reboot\par
sign \emdash  code-sign this specific file after copying\par
32bit / 64bit \emdash  when installing side-by-side files, force the correct SysWow64 vs System32 path\par
Per-file architecture override \emdash  related to the 32bit/64bit flags above; no way to mark individual files as 32-bit-only or 64-bit-only.\par
\cf0\par
\cf1 Per-file component linkage \emdash  there is no way on the Files page itself to tag a file as belonging to a specific component (this is done on the Components page, which is fine, but a quick-assign shortcut here could save clicks).\cf0\par
\par
Exclude filter when adding a folder \emdash  when the developer uses "Add Folder", everything in the folder is ingested. There is no way to specify wildcards to exclude (e.g. *.pdb, *.log, Thumbs.db). The developer has to manually remove unwanted files afterwards.\par
\par
Per-file DestDir override \emdash  all files in a tree node go to the same destination folder. There is no per-file destination override (e.g. "this one specific file should land in \{sys\} instead of \{app\}").\par
\par
\par
\b\f0\par
Page 1 \f1\emdash\f0  Registry\par
\b0\f1 Rules violation:\par
\par
The "Register in Windows Installed Programs" checkbox is created with BS_AUTOCHECKBOX (native Win32 button) \emdash  it should use CreateCustomCheckbox like every other checkbox in the app.\par
Missing Inno Setup functionality:\par
\par
AppId / uninstall GUID \emdash  The most critical missing field. Inno uses AppId to identify the application for upgrades/reinstalls. Without a stable GUID, every reinstall creates a duplicate entry in "Add/Remove Programs". Should be auto-generated (e.g. a UUID) on project creation, stored in the DB, and shown here as a read-only field the developer can override. Without this, the generated .iss will be broken for upgrades.\par
\par
Per-entry "delete on uninstall" flags \emdash  Inno supports per-entry flags on [Registry] entries for uninstall behaviour. None are currently exposed:\par
\par
deletevalue \emdash  delete this value at uninstall\par
uninsdeletevalue \emdash  delete the value only if it was created by this installer\par
deletekey \emdash  delete the entire key at uninstall\par
uninsdeletekey \emdash  delete the key at uninstall only if it was created by this installer\par
uninsdeletekeyifempty \emdash  delete key at uninstall only if it is empty by then\par
dontcreatekey \emdash  add values to an existing key without creating it if absent\par
preservestringtype \emdash  when updating a string value, don't change its existing type\par
32-bit vs 64-bit registry view \emdash  Inno supports a Flags: 32bit or 64bit per [Registry] entry to explicitly target the 32-bit (HKLM\\SOFTWARE\\WOW6432Node\\...) or 64-bit view. No selector currently exists.\par
\par
Value types \emdash  the Add Value dialog shows a type combo. Need to verify all of these are available: REG_SZ, REG_EXPAND_SZ, REG_MULTI_SZ, REG_DWORD, REG_QWORD, REG_BINARY. If any are missing, the developer cannot create entries of that type.\par
\par
Per-key/value component linkage \emdash  no way to say "only write this registry entry if component X was installed". Inno supports a Components: field on every [Registry] row.\par
\par
Per-key/value "only if doesn't exist" \emdash  related to dontcreatekey above, but also for values: write the value only if it does not already exist (common for first-run defaults).\par
\par
root: HKA shorthand \emdash  Inno has a special HKA pseudo-root that resolves to HKCU for per-user installs and HKLM for all-users installs. Without this, the developer has to manually duplicate entries for both UAC modes. No equivalent is exposed.\par
\par
\b\f0\par
Page 2 \f1\emdash\f0  Shortcuts\par
\b0\f1 What's already there: Desktop shortcut + opt-out, Start Menu tree with subfolders + "Add Shortcut Here", Pin to Start + opt-out, Pin to Taskbar + opt-out. The ShortcutDef struct has: name, exePath, workingDir, iconPath, iconIndex, runAsAdmin.\par
\par
Missing Inno Setup functionality:\par
\par
Arguments / Parameters \emdash  Inno's [Icons] section has a Parameters: field. There is no way to set command-line arguments for a shortcut (e.g. --portable, --no-splash). ShortcutDef has no arguments field.\par
\par
Comment / Description \emdash  Inno's Comment: field sets the tooltip that appears when hovering the shortcut in Explorer/Start Menu. No field exists for this. ShortcutDef has no comment field.\par
\par
Hot key \emdash  Inno's HotKey: field assigns a global keyboard shortcut to launch the app. Not exposed anywhere. ShortcutDef has no hotkey field.\par
\par
Window style \emdash  Inno's WindowStyle: supports normal, minimized, maximized. Not exposed. ShortcutDef has no windowStyle field.\par
\par
Exclude shortcut from uninstall \emdash  Inno supports Tasks: on [Icons] entries, and Flags: uninsneveruninstall on a shortcut so the uninstaller leaves it behind. No per-shortcut "keep at uninstall" toggle exists.\par
\par
Component linkage per shortcut \emdash  Like files and registry, Inno supports Components: on [Icons] rows. No way to say "only create this shortcut if component X was installed".\par
\par
AppUserModelID \emdash  Inno supports AppUserModelID: on shortcuts, which is required for proper taskbar grouping and Jump Lists on Windows 10/11. Increasingly important for modern apps. Not in ShortcutDef.\par
\par
"Also create if already exists" vs "only if doesn't exist" \emdash  Inno Flags: createonlyiffileexists creates a shortcut only when the target exe actually exists after install. Useful for optional features. Not exposed.\par
\par
Start Menu folder "Programs" vs custom path \emdash  currently the developer builds a tree, but there is no explicit way to mark which node maps to \{group\} (the DefaultGroupName) vs a deeper subfolder. The distinction matters for the generated .iss.\par
\par
\par
\b\f0 Page 3 \f1\emdash\f0  Dependencies\b0\f1\par
What's already there: ExternalDep struct covers: display_name, is_required, delivery (bundled/auto-download/redirect-url/instructions-only), install_order (before/after welcome, before/after install, custom dialog), detect_reg_key, detect_file_path, min_version, architecture (any/x64/arm64), url, silent_args, sha256, license_path, license_text, credits_text, instructions_list, offline_behavior (abort/warn/continue/skip).\par
\par
This is the most complete page in the app. The list is short:\par
\par
Missing or worth adding:\par
\par
Download timeout \emdash  no field for how long the auto-download should wait before giving up. Without this, a slow or dead server hangs the installer indefinitely. A simple integer field in seconds (default e.g. 30) would cover it.\par
\par
"Extract to temp then run" vs "run directly" \emdash  for DD_BUNDLED deps, the file is embedded in the installer. There is no toggle for whether it should be extracted to a temp folder and run from there, or streamed/run directly. Some installers (e.g. large MSIs) require a physical file on disk before they can be launched.\par
\par
Expected exit codes \emdash  by default, a silent installer returning non-zero is treated as failure. Some legitimate installers return e.g. 3010 (reboot required) or 1641 (reboot initiated). No field exists for "these exit codes are also acceptable". Without this, the dep install step may incorrectly abort.\par
\par
Max version \emdash  min_version exists but there is no max_version. Needed when a dep is incompatible with versions that are too new (rare but real \emdash  e.g. targeting a specific runtime version range).\par
\par
Per-dep component linkage \emdash  no way to say "only install this dependency if component X was selected". All deps are currently unconditional once included.\par
\par
Custom detection logic type \emdash  currently detection is either a registry key or a file path. There is no option for a version check on the detected file (e.g. "detect msvcp140.dll in \{sys\} AND version \f2\u8805?\f0  14.0"). The min_version field exists but it is unclear whether it is checked against the registry value or the file version.\par
\par
