Page 5 \emdash  Settings\par
\b0 What's already there: App name, version, publisher, publisher URL, support URL, app icon. Output folder, output filename, compression type/level, solid compression. UAC (Admin/Invoker/Highest), minimum OS (None/Win7\endash Win11). Allow uninstall, close apps before install.\par
\par
Missing \emdash  I've grouped by priority:\par
\par
Critical (broken without these)\par
AppId / GUID \emdash  The most important missing field in the entire app. Inno uses this to detect existing installations for upgrades. Without it every reinstall creates a second entry in Add/Remove Programs. Should be auto-generated on project creation, stored in the DB, shown as an editable field here with a "Regenerate" button. Goes in the Application section.\par
\par
DefaultDirName base path selector \emdash  currently always \{pf\}\\AppName. Developer must be able to choose the base: \{pf\} / \{pf64\} / \{pf32\} / \{localappdata\} / \{commonappdata\} / \{userdocs\} / custom. A combo + optional override edit field.\par
\par
Multi-language support \emdash  currently generates a single-language installer (english only). Need ability to add multiple [Languages] entries (each with a MessagesFile). Even just "English + one more" is very common. No language list or add/remove UI exists at all.\par
\par
Important (professional quality)\par
Installer .exe version resource \emdash  what you see when you right-click the installer .exe \u8594? Properties \u8594? Details. Inno keys: VersionInfoVersion, VersionInfoTextVersion, VersionInfoDescription, VersionInfoProductName, VersionInfoProductVersion, VersionInfoCompany, VersionInfoCopyright. Without these the installer's own file properties are blank, which looks unprofessional and breaks some enterprise deployment tools.\par
\par
AppCopyright \emdash  shown in the installer's about box and feeds into VersionInfoCopyright above.\par
\par
PrivilegesRequiredOverridesAllowed \emdash  works together with the existing UAC radio buttons. Controls whether the end user can switch between per-user and all-users install at runtime. Values: none, commandline, dialog. Without dialog, the For Me/All Users wizard page (which already exists on the Dialogs page) has no effect.\par
\par
WizardStyle \emdash  modern (Windows 10-style sidebar bitmap, default in Inno 6) vs classic (old Inno 5 style with top banner). A simple combo. Developers distributing to enterprise environments sometimes need classic.\par
\par
Code signing (SignTool) \emdash  path to signtool.exe, certificate thumbprint or PFX path, timestamp URL. Without this, the generated .exe triggers SmartScreen on every install. A "Sign installer" section with enable checkbox + fields.\par
\par
Useful (developer convenience)\par
DisableDirPage \emdash  toggle to hide the "Where to install?" wizard page. Common for apps that must always go in a fixed location.\par
\par
DisableProgramGroupPage \emdash  toggle to hide the Start Menu group selection page.\par
\par
UsePreviousAppDir / UsePreviousGroup \emdash  remember last chosen install path across upgrades. Currently would always reset to DefaultDirName.\par
\par
DirExistsWarning \emdash  warn the user if the destination folder already exists (yes / no / auto). Currently Inno defaults to auto; developer may want to force it off for upgrade scenarios.\par
\par
SetupMutex \emdash  a named mutex to prevent two copies of the installer running simultaneously. No field for this.\par
\par
ChangesEnvironment \emdash  flag that broadcasts a WM_SETTINGCHANGE after install, needed when the installer adds to the system PATH.\par
\par
ChangesAssociations \emdash  same broadcast for file associations. Needed for any app that registers file types.\par
\par
SetupLogging / LogMode \emdash  enable Inno's built-in setup log and control whether it appends or overwrites. Useful for enterprise deployments and support.\par
\par
UninstallDisplayName \emdash  override the name shown in Windows "Add/Remove Programs" (defaults to AppName, but some publishers prefer e.g. AppName 2.0 (64-bit)).\par
\par
UninstallFilesDir \emdash  where the uninstaller .exe is placed (default \{app\}; some developers put it in \{commonappdata\} for shared installs).\par
\par
LanguageDetectionMethod \emdash  uilanguage / locale / none. Controls how Inno picks the default language when the installer starts.\par
\par
WizardResizable \emdash  whether the installer window can be resized by the end user. Defaults to no in Inno 6.\par
\par
