\b Page 8 \emdash  Scripts\b0\par
What's already there: Master enable checkbox, tile-grid ListView, Add/Load/Edit/Delete buttons. Script types: batch and PowerShell. When-to-run: Before Files, After Files, Finish opt-out, Uninstall. Editor has: name, type radios, when combo, run hidden, wait for completion, also-run-at-uninstall, finish-page label, script content editor (Scintilla + syntax highlighting), load from file, test in terminal. sort_order field exists in ScriptRow.\par
\par
Missing or worth adding:\par
\par
"Fail silently" vs "abort install on error" per script \emdash  if a script exits with a non-zero code, there is no per-script toggle for whether the install should abort or continue. Currently there is no on_error field in ScriptRow. Very important for optional post-install steps.\par
\par
Working directory \emdash  Inno's [Run] section has a WorkingDir: field. There is no field in ScriptRow or the editor for setting the working directory of the script process. Without this, relative paths inside scripts may break.\par
\par
Parameters / arguments \emdash  Inno's [Run] has a Parameters: field. The script content itself is the script body, but for "run an external exe" scenarios a parameters field is needed. Less critical for bat/ps1 but still applicable.\par
\par
Finish opt-out "checked by default" toggle \emdash  for SWR_FINISH_OPTOUT scripts, Inno's [Run] Flags: postinstall defaults the checkbox to unchecked. There is no toggle to make it checked by default (checked flag in Inno). The description field is already there for the label text, but the default-checked state is missing.\par
\par
Drag-to-reorder within a when-to-run group \emdash  sort_order exists in ScriptRow but there is no drag-and-drop or up/down button UI to let the developer change execution order. Order matters \emdash  script 1 may need to run before script 2.\par
\par
Component linkage per script \emdash  no way to say "only run this script if component X was installed". No component_id field in ScriptRow.\par
\par
"Run elevated" toggle per script \emdash  some scripts need admin privileges regardless of the installer's UAC level. Inno's [Run] supports Flags: runascurrentuser vs runasoriginaluser. No per-script elevation override exists.\par
\par
Description visible in the tile \emdash  the ListView shows tiles but only the script name is displayed. The description field (finish-page label text) is not visible in the tile grid, so there is no at-a-glance summary of what each script does. A separate notes/description field for the tile label (distinct from the finish-page label) would help.\par
\par
