\b Page 9 \emdash  Components\b0\par
What's already there: Enable checkbox, split-pane (folder tree left, component list right), Edit button. ComponentRow has: display_name, description, notes_rtf, is_required, is_preselected, source_type (file/folder), source_path, dest_path, dependencies (inter-component).\par
\par
Missing or worth adding:\par
\par
Install types ("Full / Compact / Custom") \emdash  Inno's [Types] section defines named install presets. Each type pre-selects a different set of components. The end user picks a type from a dropdown on the Components wizard page and the checkboxes update accordingly. There is no concept of install types at all \emdash  no types list, no per-component type membership. Without this, the Components wizard page in the generated installer will have no presets dropdown, which Inno shows by default.\par
\par
Component groups (GroupDescription) \emdash  Inno supports visually grouping components under a collapsible heading in the wizard. Currently the list is flat. A group or parent_id field in ComponentRow would enable this, and the edit dialog would need a group picker.\par
\par
Fixed flag (always installed, shown greyed-out) \emdash  distinct from is_required. Inno's Flags: fixed shows the component in the wizard UI but locks it (checked and greyed, cannot be deselected). The current is_required hides the component from the UI entirely (installs silently). Both behaviours are valid and serve different purposes. No is_fixed field exists in ComponentRow.\par
\par
Exclusive flag (radio-button style) \emdash  Inno's Flags: exclusive makes a group of components behave like radio buttons \emdash  selecting one deselects all others in the group. Useful for "Edition: Standard / Professional / Enterprise" scenarios. No is_exclusive field exists.\par
\par
Disk space / size display \emdash  Inno's [Components] section has a ExtraDiskSpaceRequired: field (in bytes). The wizard page shows a running total of disk space needed as the user ticks/unticks components. No size field exists in ComponentRow and there is no auto-calculation.\par
\par
Restart flag per component \emdash  Inno supports Flags: restart on a component to signal that a reboot is required after installing that specific component. No per-component restart flag exists.\par
\par
Inter-component dependency display \emdash  ComponentRow.dependencies exists and is persisted, but it is unclear whether the generated .iss uses it to enforce Inno's [Components] Flags: dontinheritcheck or similar. Inno does not natively enforce component dependencies in its UI; this would need [Code] script logic. Worth documenting or surfacing a warning to the developer.\par
